grexa (1.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rename the application ID to com.visorcraft.Grexa (desktop file,
    AppStream component, icon names, D-Bus/Wayland app_id, and the Secret
    Service keyring service) and set the organization domain to
    visorcraft.com. Breaking identity change: earlier installs do not
    upgrade in place and previously stored API keys are not carried over
    to the new keyring service.

 -- VisorCraft LLC <maintainer@visorcraft.com>  Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

grexa (1.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security hardening: replace stays within the search root and restores
    permissions via the file descriptor; AI API keys are never sent over
    plaintext HTTP and are redacted from logs; bounded regex backtracking,
    a 512 MiB search read cap, and a pdftotext watchdog guard pathological
    inputs; container exec/cp argument-injection hardening; CLI
    terminal-escape sanitization.
  * API keys now use the pure-Rust Secret Service keyring backend.
  * Hardened release CI (pinned actions + image digests, build provenance).
  * Removed dead code and unused dependencies.

 -- VisorCraft LLC <maintainer@visorcraft.com>  Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

